93 



trade union congress, whose leadership were SPD members, was 
in contradiction of party policy. A secret meeting of SPD and 
union leaders in February 1906 agreed, however, that the Jena 
resolution would be quiedy buried — and the SPD’s 1906 Con- 
gress officially declared that there was no contradiction between 
the Jena resolution and the trade union position adopted at 
Cologne. 

10. The Russian Social Democratic Party (rsdlp), which was to 
divide into two wings at its 1903 Congress: the Bolsheviks and 
Mensheviks. 

1 1 . War broke out between Russia and Japan in Febuary 1904. It 
ended within the year in defeat for Russia. 

12. The Tsar’s mounted troops, noted for their brutality. 

13. Sergei Zubatov was chief of the Tsarist police in Moscow. He 
organised workers into ‘unions’ under police auspices as a way 
of trying to prevent strikes. 

14. Osvoboshdenye was the paper published abroad by the Russian 
Liberals. Peter Struve, its editor, was a former Social Democrat. 

15. The ruling clique. 

16. Along with the eight-hour day, the petition to be presented to 
the Tsar also asked for freedom of speech and the press, the 
separation of church and state, land for the peasants, freedom of 
assembly for the workers, an end to the war with Japan, and the 
calling of a Constituent Assembly. 

17. The Tsar’s troops fired on the crowd, then horsemen charged 
with sabres. The exact figures are unknown, but more than a 
thousand people were killed and many more wounded. 

18. The zemstvos were rural assemblies, dominated by the nobility 
and the Liberals and with severely limited powers. 

19. Both Poland and Lithuania were ruled by Russia in 1905. Rosa 
Luxemburg managed to smuggle herself into Poland in Decem- 
ber 1905 and remained there until she was arrested in March 
1906. The information here concerning the extent of the strikes 
she presumably collected personally. 

20. This is the Petersburg Soviet. 

2 1 . Bulygin was the Tsar’s minister for the interior. In response to 
the mass strikes of 1905, the government offered to set up a 



